<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: LAKE PERRIS SWIMMING WITH REGULAR-SIZE BASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Castaic and Casitas might be the lakes for trophy-sized largemouth bass, but 
Riverside County's Lake Perris seems to be the place for regular bass. 
</P>
<P>
 "Guys have been catching 25 bass a day," said Mark Hamann, an employee at the 
lake.  
</P>
<P>
 The bass have moved into the shallows to spawn. They are averaging only 14 
inches, Hamann said, but there are exceptions. Ted Ford of Los Angeles landed 
an 8-pound 12-ounce bass while fishing a Power Worm at the dam, and Gary 
Marshman of Murrieta caught a 6-pounder while fishing a plastic worm at the 
east end. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
