<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VENICE; RESIDENT SHOOTS 
SCREAMING HOME INTRUDER TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Venice resident early Tuesday shot and killed a man who had barged into his 
home screaming obscenities, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they received a complaint about a man shouting and banging on cars 
on Brooks Avenue near Ocean Front Walk. After the man broke through the front 
door of 44-year-old Tak Cho's home yelling obscenities, Cho shot him in the 
chest with a large-caliber handgun, said Detective Cedric Wilder of the Los 
Angeles Police Department's Pacific Division. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified man was pronounced dead by paramedics. Police said they 
confiscated Cho's gun. A decision on whether charges will be filed against Cho 
will not be made until an investigation by the district attorney's office is 
completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
