<P>
JERUSALEM POLICY THE SAME, U.S. SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dismissing reports of a policy change, the State Department on Tuesday 
reaffirmed the U.S. position that the final status of Jerusalem should be 
decided by the parties in negotiations. 
</P>
<P>
 "There has been no change in our position on Jerusalem," State Department 
spokesman Mike McCurry said. He attributed the confusion to an "erroneous press 
report." 
</P>
</TEXT>
