ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; STUDENT PROGRAM AT CAL STATE HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LILY DIZON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Cal State Fullerton student program called the Student Leadership Institute 
has won the 1994 Distinguished Student Development Program Award given by the 
National Assn. for Campus Activities Educational Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 The award recognizes quality student-development programs at colleges and 
universities.The Student Leadership Institute, like programs that have won the 
award in the past, becomes part of a library of model programs to be used by 
the Commission for Student Development. 
</P>
<P>
 The institute program offers workshops that improve leadership skills such as 
time and stress management, communication skills and how to tackle race and 
gender issues, according to Nargess Akhavi, a student coordinator for the 
institute. 
</P>
<P>
 About 550 students participated in the different workshops offered by the 
institute this school year. LILY DIZON 
</P>
