<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEEN-AGER KILLED IN WEEKEND TRAFFIC DISPUTE IS IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police Tuesday identified the victim killed in a weekend shootout as a 
17-year-old Santa Ana boy. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas Rodriguez was shot Saturday when what police described as a deadly game 
of cat and mouse between two moving vehicles erupted into gunfire, according to 
Lt. David Nick. 
</P>
<P>
 A dispute between passengers in the two vehicles, which were traveling along 
city streets, apparently led to the shootings, police said. Rodriguez was shot 
in the head, and a second man, Ramon Martinez, 26, also of Santa Ana, was shot 
in the back, Nick said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not made it clear which cars the two shooting victims were in. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said they believe that some of those in the autos were gang 
members. No arrests have been made. 
</P>
</TEXT>
